the mad definition facility.wone of the first definition facilities forhigher level languages is described.  users of the language can define new operators and/or data typesinto the mad language, so that their use appears as if they were predefined.  information is given onhow one writes definitions, as well as on much of the motivation behind the form in which definitions arewritten. some conclusions are drawn about future definitional facilities.cacm august, arden, b. w.galler, b. a.graham, r. m..kmad, definitions, operators, macros, higher level language.c. .ca jb february ,   : pm